---

Wash and dry all produce. Preheat the broiler to high. Soak the @wooden skewers{4} in water. Take @butter{1.5%tablespoon} out of the fridge to come to room temperature. Core, seed, and dice the @red bell pepper{1} into ¾-inch cubes. Halve, peel, and dice the @shallot{1} into ¾-inch pieces. Finely chop the @oregano{¼%ounce} leaves (you'll need about 1 teaspoon).

Toss the @beef tenderloin tips{12%ounce} in a #large bowl{} with the bell pepper, shallot, 1 teaspoon oregano, half the @chipotle powder{1%teaspoon}, and a drizzle of @olive oil{2%teaspoon}. Season generously with @salt{} and @pepper{}. Thread the beef, peppers, and shallot onto the skewers, alternating between each.

Place the @corn on the cob{2} onto a #baking sheet{} and rub with a drizzle of olive oil. Season with salt and pepper. Place under the broiler for ~{5%minutes}, until slightly charred.

Cook the skewers: Remove the baking sheet from the oven and flip the corn. Place the skewers alongside the corn and place under the broiler for another ~{5-8%minutes}, turning once, until lightly charred and cooked to desired doneness.

Meanwhile, zest and cut the @lime{1} into wedges. In a #small bowl{}, combine the butter, a squeeze of lime, a pinch of lime zest, and as much remaining chipotle powder as you like (add a little and go up from there!). Season with salt and pepper.

> TIP: If you like your corn slathered with butter, feel free to up the butter amount. We won't tell!

Finish: Serve the corn rubbed with the chipotle-lime butter. Brush any remaining butter over the skewers, if desired. Finish with a squeeze of lime and enjoy!